I really wanted to put 3.5 stars but I don't think it was an option. I have indulged in Mexican food across state lines, bars, pubs, restaurants, and homes as well as many a margarita but I always find it difficult to step into an establishment with the great hope of good food. I ordered a more traditional Asada taco with cilantro, onions, and lime, in addition, a barbacoa taco with the same toppings. The steak was pleasant on its own and grew in flavor once I added ghost pepper hot sauce. The barbacoa left something to be desired, but palatable nonetheless. I ordered a horchata with rum and it wasn't a true replication of the lightly sweet cinnamon rice water I'm used to. I would go back for the Asada tacos on Tuesdays for sure.
